<TITLE> Aila 'cost fisheries Tk 312 crore' in SW </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, June 6 (bdnews24.com)  Losses to fisheries after Cyclone Aila stands at Tk 312 crore in four south-western districts, said minister Abdul Latif Biswas visiting the region on Saturday. He said livestock saw losses of around Tk 16 crore in the four districts of Bagherhat, Khulna, Pirojpur and Sathkhira in the wake of last month's cyclone. Speaking to reporters at the Khulna Press Club, the fisheries and livestock minister said shrimp farmers with little capital will be helped to recover losses. He added that long-term initiatives would be undertaken for expansion and improvement of shrimp cultivation under the fair shrimp and hatchery guidelines. But Biswas came down heavy on shrimp farmers for undermining flood embankments by illegal pumping of water to fill their enclosures. He asked the shrimp farm owners to desist from such destructive activities. Biswas said shrimp farmers with little capital will be helped to recover losses. He added that long-term initiatives would be undertaken for expansion and improvement of shrimp cultivation under the fair shrimp and hatchery guidelines. He said embankments along the Bagherhat, Khulna and Satkhira coastal belt would be rebuilt with support of the army after on a priority basis according to extent of damage. "The government has made all out efforts to provide shelter and drinking water to cyclone victims made homeless." The minister also distributed cash, rice and cow feed among the cyclone-hit in Bagherhat on Saturday. bdnews24.
